[2026-03-19T09:49:13.309Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E1Gu5fsFsuPsUk5357FSL8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I now have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed summary document:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE CODEBASE EXPLORATION REPORT\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of your personas-cloud codebase, here's a complete understanding of all the major components:\n\n---\n\n### 1. DATABASE LAYER ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Technology Stack:**\n- **ORM/Driver**: `better-sqlite3` (native SQLite driver for Node.js)\n- **Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/`\n\n**Database Files:**\n- `schema.ts` - Defines all SQL schemas, migrations, and database initialization\n- `_helpers.ts` - Helper functions: statement caching, WHERE clause building, row mappers\n- `executions.ts` - Persona execution CRUD operations\n- `events.ts` - Event publishing and subscriptions\n- `triggers.ts` - Trigger configuration and scheduling\n- `personas.ts` - Persona CRUD operations\n- `credentials.ts` - Credential management\n- `tools.ts` - Tool definitions and linking\n- `triggerFires.ts` - Trigger fire history and statistics\n- `inferenceProfiles.ts` - Inference provider profiles\n- `index.ts` - Barrel exports for all DB modules\n\n**Key Implementation Patterns:**\n1. **Statement Caching**: `stmt()` function caches prepared statements per (db, sql) pair using WeakMap\n2. **Row Mappers**: Generic `createRowMapper<T>()` converts database rows to TypeScript types\n3. **Dynamic WHERE Clauses**: `buildWhereClause()` builds parameterized WHERE clauses from filter objects\n4. **Transactions**: SQLite transactions for atomic multi-step operations (e.g., metric aggregation)\n\n---\n\n### 2. PERSONA_EXECUTIONS TABLE SCHEMA\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (lines 198-223)\n\n**Complete Column Definition**:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_executions (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  trigger_id TEXT,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  event_id TEXT,                        -- bidirectional event↔execution tracing\n  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued' -- CHECK(status IN ('queued','running','completed','failed','cancelled'))\n  input_data TEXT,\n  output_data TEXT,\n  claude_session_id TEXT,\n  model_used TEXT,\n  input_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,       -- metrizable column (aggregated into daily_metrics)\n  output_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,      -- metrizable column\n  cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,              -- metrizable column (SUM during retention)\n  error_message TEXT,\n  duration_ms INTEGER,                  -- metrizable column (SUM during retention)\n  retry_of_execution_id TEXT,\n  retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  started_at TEXT,\n  completed_at TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL              -- temporal column used for retention cutoff\n);\n```\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_pex_persona` on `(persona_id)`\n- `idx_pex_status` on `(status)`\n- `idx_pex_created_status` on `(created_at, status)` — critical for retention queries\n- `idx_pex_project` on `(project_id)` — added during migrations for multi-tenancy\n\n**Metrizable Columns** (aggregated before purge via TABLE_REGISTRY):\n- `cost_usd` - aggregation: SUM\n- `duration_ms` - aggregation: SUM\n- `input_tokens` - aggregation: SUM\n- `output_tokens` - aggregation: SUM\n\n**Row Mapper** (in executions.ts):\nMaps database snake_case to TypeScript camelCase: `persona_id` → `personaId`, `cost_usd` → `costUsd`, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 3. RETENTION JOB SYSTEM\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts`\n\n**How It Works**:\n\n1. **Scheduling**: Wall-clock daily trigger (not drifting setInterval)\n   - First check 5 seconds after startup\n   - Periodic checks every 60 seconds\n   - Runs exactly once per UTC calendar day (via `system_kv` persistence)\n\n2. **State Persistence** (in `system_kv` table):\n   - `retention_last_run_date` - YYYY-MM-DD of last run (prevents double-execution)\n   - `retention_last_run_at` - ISO timestamp for health endpoint\n\n3. **Retention Policies** (defined as RetentionPolicy instances):\n   - `execPolicy`: Deletes completed/failed/cancelled executions older than `retentionDays`\n   - `eventsPolicy`: Deletes delivered/skipped/failed events older than `retentionDays`\n   - `stuckEventsPolicy`: Deletes stuck pending/processing events older than `retentionDays * 7` (7x longer grace period)\n   - `dailyMetricsPolicy`: Deletes old daily metrics older than `metricsRetentionDays`\n   - `systemDailyMetricsPolicy`: Deletes system-wide aggregated metrics\n\n4. **Execution Flow**:\n   ```\n   tick() → check if today != lastRunDate\n        ↓\n        → runRetention():\n           ├─ For each tenant:\n           │  ├─ purge persona_executions (status-filtered)\n           │  ├─ purge persona_events (status-filtered)\n           │  ├─ purge stuck events (7-day grace)\n           │  └─ purge daily_metrics\n           │\n           ├─ aggregateSystemMetrics():\n           │  ├─ Read daily_metrics from all tenant DBs\n           │  ├─ Accumulate totals by date\n           │  └─ Upsert into system_daily_metrics\n           │\n           └─ purge system_daily_metrics\n        ↓\n        → persist lastRunDate + lastRunAt\n        ↓\n        → log health metrics (tenantsProcessed, rowsDeleted per table, errors)\n   ```\n\n5. **Chunked Deletion** (via RetentionPolicy.purge()):\n   - Counts total rows & candidates (WHERE created_at < cutoff AND status IN (...))\n   - Aborts if candidates/total > maxPurgeFraction (safety cap, default 0.8)\n   - Deletes in chunks of 5000 rows per batch\n   - Yields event loop between batches (setImmediate) to keep system responsive\n\n**Health Metrics** (RetentionHealth interface):\n```typescript\n{\n  lastRunAt: string | null;\n  lastRunDurationMs: number | null;\n  retentionDays: number;\n  metricsRetentionDays: number;\n  totalRuns: number;\n  totalErrors: number;\n  running: boolean;\n  lastRun: RetentionRunMetrics | null; // detailed per-run stats\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. RETENTION POLICY MECHANISM\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts`\n\n**Architecture**:\n- `RetentionPolicyConfig` interface: `{ table, chunkSize?, deleteFilter? }`\n- Reads spec from TABLE_REGISTRY at construction time (single source of truth)\n- Encapsulates: cutoff logic, safety-fraction checks, chunked delete with yields\n\n**Key Methods**:\n```typescript\nasync purge(\n  db: Database.Database,\n  cutoff: string,              // ISO timestamp for age filtering\n  logger: Logger,\n  context?: Record<string, unknown>\n): Promise<number>             // returns total rows deleted\n```\n\n**Safety Mechanisms**:\n1. Pre-purge sanity check: count total rows vs candidates\n2. Abort if `candidates/total > maxPurgeFraction` (logs error and returns 0)\n3. Chunked delete: prevents long lock durations (~50ms per chunk)\n4. Event-loop yields: keeps system responsive during multi-tenant runs\n\n---\n\n### 5. HTTP API PATTERNS\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` (39,563 bytes)\n\n**Architecture**: Two-tier routing system\n\n**Tier 1: Exact-Path Routes** (O(1) lookup by `METHOD:/path`)\n- Stored in `exactRoutes` Map\n- Used for static endpoints like `/api/status`, `/api/execute`, `/api/oauth/*`, `/api/admin/*`\n- Example: `exactRoutes.set('GET:/api/status', { handler: ... })`\n\n**Tier 2: Resource-Based Routes** (O(1) lookup by `METHOD:resource[:id][:subResource]`)\n- Stored in `resourceRoutes` Map\n- Key function: `resourceKey(method, resource, hasId, subResource)` → `\"METHOD:resource[:id][:subResource]\"`\n- Parsed from URL via `parseRoute(pathname)` → `{ resource, id?, subResource? }`\n- Examples:\n  - `GET /api/personas` → `GET:personas`\n  - `POST /api/personas` → `POST:personas`\n  - `GET /api/personas/{id}` → `GET:personas:id`\n  - `GET /api/personas/{id}/tools` → `GET:personas:id:tools`\n  - `POST /api/personas/{id}/tools` → `POST:personas:id:tools`\n\n**RouteEntry Structure**:\n```typescript\n{\n  handler: RouteHandler;\n  needsDb?: boolean;      // requires tenantDb to be available\n  adminOnly?: boolean;    // requires auth.authType === 'admin'\n}\n```\n\n**Common Handler Signature**:\n```typescript\ntype RouteHandler = (\n  req: http.IncomingMessage,\n  res: http.ServerResponse,\n  ctx: RequestContext,             // { authType, projectId, userEmail }\n  route: ParsedRoute | null,\n  queryString: string | undefined,\n  tenantDb: Database.Database | undefined,\n  scopedProjectId: string | undefined,\n  reqLogger: Logger,\n) => Promise<void> | void;\n```\n\n**Request Processing Flow**:\n1. Parse URL → extract route, query string\n2. Auth check via `auth.validateAndExtractContext(req)`\n3. Determine scoped project (null if admin auth)\n4. Resolve database: single-tenant or per-tenant via TenantDbManager\n5. O(1) exact-path lookup → if hit, call handler\n6. O(1) resource-route lookup via `resourceKey()` → if hit, call handler\n7. Otherwise 404\n\n**Middleware Patterns**:\n- `withHttpAudit(handler, action, resourceType)` - wraps mutation handlers to emit audit events\n- `withScopedEntity(entity, scopedProjectId, res)` - validates ownership + returns entity or sends 404\n- `requireAdmin(ctx, res)` - checks admin access, returns 403 if not\n\n**Error Handling**:\n- Payload too large (>1MB) → 413\n- UNIQUE constraint violation → 409 Conflict\n- Unhandled errors → 500 with `X-Request-Id` header\n\n**Standard Response Format**:\n- `httpUtils.json(res, status, data)` - writes JSON with Content-Type header\n\n---\n\n### 6. TRIGGER SCHEDULER SYSTEM\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts`\n\n**Architecture**: Heap-driven scheduler with in-memory hot path\n\n**Key Components**:\n\n**Heap Data Structure** (`TriggerHeap` in triggerHeap.ts):\n- Min-heap keyed by `nextTriggerAt` (epoch ms)\n- O(log n) push/pop/remove operations\n- Maintains `triggerId → index` Map for O(log n) updates\n- Database remains source of truth; heap is hot-path cache\n\n**Initialization** (Bootstrap Phase):\n1. If `tenantDbManager`: iterate each tenant, load enabled triggers\n2. If single `database`: load all triggers\n3. Populate heap with `{ triggerId, tenantId, nextTriggerAt }`\n4. Log summary: heapSize, duration, failedTenants\n\n**Scheduler Loop**:\n```\nEvery 100-60000ms (computed dynamically):\n  1. Pop all due entries (nextTriggerAt <= now)\n  2. Group by tenantId for batch DB access\n  3. For each tenant:\n     - Fetch triggers by IDs\n     - Skip polling triggers\n     - Detect missed triggers (latency > 60s)\n     - Publish events to persona_events table\n     - Record trigger_fires entry\n     - Compute next trigger time\n     - Push updated time back into heap\n  4. Update metrics (triggersFiredTotal, triggersMissedTotal)\n  5. Schedule next tick based on heap peek (MIN_DELAY_MS, MAX_DELAY_MS)\n```\n\n**Missed Trigger Detection**:\n- Compares scheduled time vs actual fire time\n- Logs warning if latency > MAX_DELAY_MS (60s)\n- Triggers fired late but still recorded\n\n**Metrics** (SchedulerMetrics):\n```typescript\n{\n  heap_size: number;\n  next_due_at: string | null;\n  triggers_fired_total: number;\n  triggers_missed_total: number;\n  avg_tick_latency_ms: number;\n  last_tick_at: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Heartbeat**: Every 60 seconds logs aggregate metrics + per-tick missed counts\n\n**API** (TriggerSchedulerHandle):\n- `close()` - stops scheduler\n- `nudge()` - reschedule immediately (after trigger CRUD)\n- `heapPush(triggerId, tenantId, nextTriggerAt)` - push/update in heap\n- `heapRemove(triggerId)` - remove from heap\n- `getMetrics()` - return current metrics\n\n---\n\n### 7. TENANT DB MANAGER\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/tenantDbManager.ts`\n\n**Architecture**: Per-tenant SQLite database with connection pooling\n\n**Layout**:\n```\n{dataDir}/\n  ├─ system.db           — tenant registry + global state (system_kv, system_daily_metrics)\n  └─ tenants/\n     ├─ {hash1}.db       — tenant 1 database\n     ├─ {hash2}.db       — tenant 2 database\n     └─ ...\n```\n\n**Hash Function**: `crypto.sha256(projectId).slice(0, 16)` — safe filenames\n\n**Connection Pooling**:\n- `CachedDb` interface: `{ db: Database.Database, lastAccess: number }`\n- Maps `projectId → CachedDb`\n- Auto-eviction: idle > 10 minutes (IDLE_EVICT_MS)\n- Eviction check: every 1 minute (EVICT_CHECK_MS)\n\n**Key Methods**:\n1. `getTenantDb(projectId)` — get or create + auto-register in system.db\n2. `getSystemDb()` — access system database\n3. `listTenantIds()` — all registered tenants from system.db\n4. `forEachTenant(fn)` — execute function for each tenant\n5. `getHealthStats()` — per-tenant file size, row counts, oldest record age\n6. `close()` — shutdown all connections + stop eviction timer\n\n**Tenant Registration**:\n- On first `getTenantDb(projectId)` access\n- Inserts into `tenants` table in system.db\n- Calls optional `onTenantCreated` callback for key warming\n\n**Health Stats** (DbHealthStats):\n```typescript\n{\n  totalSizeBytes: number;\n  tenantCount: number;\n  totalExecutionRows: number;\n  totalEventRows: number;\n  oldestUnpurgedAgeMs: number | null;\n  perTenant: Array<{\n    projectId: string;\n    sizeBytes: number;\n    executionRows: number;\n    eventRows: number;\n    oldestRecordAge: string | null;\n  }>;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. TABLE REGISTRY (SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH)\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`\n\n**Purpose**: Declarative classification of time-series tables for retention lifecycle\n\n**Lifecycle Categories**:\n- **Metrizable**: numeric columns aggregated into summary table before purge\n- **Ephemeral**: rows deleted after retention window without pre-purge aggregation\n\n**Registry** (TABLE_REGISTRY constant):\n\n| Table | Lifecycle | Timestamp Column | Metrizable Columns | Aggregation Target | Max Purge % |\n|-------|-----------|------------------|--------------------|--------------------|------------|\n| `persona_executions` | Metrizable | `created_at` | cost_usd (SUM), duration_ms (SUM), input_tokens (SUM), output_tokens (SUM) | `daily_metrics` | 80% |\n| `persona_events` | Ephemeral | `created_at` | — | — | 80% |\n| `audit_events` | Ephemeral | `timestamp` | — | — (90-day min retention) | 80% |\n| `trigger_fires` | Ephemeral | `fired_at` | — | — | 80% |\n| `daily_metrics` | Ephemeral | `date` | — | — | 80% |\n| `system_daily_metrics` | Ephemeral | `date` | — | — | 80% |\n\n**Helper Functions**:\n- `getTableSpec(tableName)` — lookup by name\n- `getTablesByLifecycle(lifecycle)` — filter by category\n- `isMetrizable(spec)` / `isEphemeral(spec)` — type guards\n\n**Design Principle**: Retention engine consults this registry at runtime, not hard-coded in procedural code\n\n---\n\n### 9. ADDITIONAL KEY PATTERNS\n\n**Event-Driven Architecture**:\n- Events published to `persona_events` table with status `'pending'`\n- Event processor picks up pending events and transitions through states\n- Event subscriptions match event types to personas\n- Retry logic with exponential backoff via `retry_after` column\n\n**Multi-Tenancy Model**:\n- Single-tenant mode: one `database` + all personas in `project_id='default'`\n- Multi-tenant mode: `tenantDbManager` with per-tenant DBs\n- Project scoping: queries filter by `project_id` when in user auth context (not admin)\n\n**Trigger Types**:\n- `schedule`: cron expressions or \"every Xm/h/s/d\" shorthand\n- `manual`: triggered by external API call\n- `polling`: checked periodically (not auto-fired by scheduler)\n- `webhook`: received via HTTP POST\n- `chain`: triggered by output of another persona\n\n**Metrics Aggregation**:\n- Per-execution: cost_usd, duration_ms, input/output_tokens recorded in `persona_executions`\n- Per-day rollup: `updateExecution()` auto-increments `daily_metrics` on terminal status transition\n- Per-system: retention job aggregates all tenant `daily_metrics` → `system_daily_metrics`\n\n**Audit Trail** (append-only):\n- Separate database (audit.db) via `AuditLog` class\n- SHA-256 hash chain for integrity verification\n- Discriminated union of entry types (key:encrypt, persona:create, etc.)\n- Query/stats/verify operations via dedicated methods\n\n---\n\n### 10. CRITICAL FILES REFERENCE\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` | All SQL schemas, migrations, DB initialization |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/executions.ts` | Persona execution CRUD, metrics recording |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts` | Daily retention job scheduling & execution |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts` | RetentionPolicy class: safety checks, chunked deletes |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` | HTTP server, exact-path + resource routing |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts` | Heap-driven trigger scheduler |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/tenantDbManager.ts` | Per-tenant DB pool manager |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts` | TABLE_REGISTRY: metrizable/ephemeral lifecycle classification |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/_helpers.ts` | Statement caching, WHERE builders, row mappers |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerHeap.ts` | TriggerHeap: min-heap implementation |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/index.ts` | Main entry point, component initialization |\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive exploration covers all the architectural patterns, data models, and operational mechanisms of your personas-cloud orchestrator system. Every major component has been analyzed with complete understanding of how data flows through the system, how retention works, how triggers fire, and how HTTP APIs are registered and dispatched."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae6574dd01fbec8aa (use SendMessage with to: 'ae6574dd01fbec8aa' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 83049\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 93330</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f83562c4-7cd5-4d50-b7ac-458d47ebaf2f","uuid":"ff9518e5-a8d3-42ab-afa5-a40aae0ff47e","timestamp":"2026-03-19T09:49:13.216Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The database layer - how tables are defined, how queries are made, what ORM/driver is used. Look in packages/orchestrator/src/db/ and any migration files.\n2. The persona_executions table schema - what columns exist, especially status, cost_usd, duration_ms, tokens, persona_id fields.\n3. The retention job - how it runs, where it's scheduled, look at packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts and packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts\n4. The HTTP API patterns - how endpoints are registered, middleware, request/response patterns. Look at packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts and any handler files.\n5. The trigger scheduler - how periodic jobs are scheduled, look at packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts\n6. The tenant DB manager - packages/orchestrator/src/tenantDbManager.ts\n7. The table registry - packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts\n\nRead all relevant files fully. I need complete understanding of patterns used.","agentId":"ae6574dd01fbec8aa","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I now have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed summary document:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE CODEBASE EXPLORATION REPORT\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of your personas-cloud codebase, here's a complete understanding of all the major components:\n\n---\n\n### 1. DATABASE LAYER ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Technology Stack:**\n- **ORM/Driver**: `better-sqlite3` (native SQLite driver for Node.js)\n- **Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/`\n\n**Database Files:**\n- `schema.ts` - Defines all SQL schemas, migrations, and database initialization\n- `_helpers.ts` - Helper functions: statement caching, WHERE clause building, row mappers\n- `executions.ts` - Persona execution CRUD operations\n- `events.ts` - Event publishing and subscriptions\n- `triggers.ts` - Trigger configuration and scheduling\n- `personas.ts` - Persona CRUD operations\n- `credentials.ts` - Credential management\n- `tools.ts` - Tool definitions and linking\n- `triggerFires.ts` - Trigger fire history and statistics\n- `inferenceProfiles.ts` - Inference provider profiles\n- `index.ts` - Barrel exports for all DB modules\n\n**Key Implementation Patterns:**\n1. **Statement Caching**: `stmt()` function caches prepared statements per (db, sql) pair using WeakMap\n2. **Row Mappers**: Generic `createRowMapper<T>()` converts database rows to TypeScript types\n3. **Dynamic WHERE Clauses**: `buildWhereClause()` builds parameterized WHERE clauses from filter objects\n4. **Transactions**: SQLite transactions for atomic multi-step operations (e.g., metric aggregation)\n\n---\n\n### 2. PERSONA_EXECUTIONS TABLE SCHEMA\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (lines 198-223)\n\n**Complete Column Definition**:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_executions (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  trigger_id TEXT,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  event_id TEXT,                        -- bidirectional event↔execution tracing\n  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued' -- CHECK(status IN ('queued','running','completed','failed','cancelled'))\n  input_data TEXT,\n  output_data TEXT,\n  claude_session_id TEXT,\n  model_used TEXT,\n  input_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,       -- metrizable column (aggregated into daily_metrics)\n  output_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,      -- metrizable column\n  cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,              -- metrizable column (SUM during retention)\n  error_message TEXT,\n  duration_ms INTEGER,                  -- metrizable column (SUM during retention)\n  retry_of_execution_id TEXT,\n  retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  started_at TEXT,\n  completed_at TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL              -- temporal column used for retention cutoff\n);\n```\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_pex_persona` on `(persona_id)`\n- `idx_pex_status` on `(status)`\n- `idx_pex_created_status` on `(created_at, status)` — critical for retention queries\n- `idx_pex_project` on `(project_id)` — added during migrations for multi-tenancy\n\n**Metrizable Columns** (aggregated before purge via TABLE_REGISTRY):\n- `cost_usd` - aggregation: SUM\n- `duration_ms` - aggregation: SUM\n- `input_tokens` - aggregation: SUM\n- `output_tokens` - aggregation: SUM\n\n**Row Mapper** (in executions.ts):\nMaps database snake_case to TypeScript camelCase: `persona_id` → `personaId`, `cost_usd` → `costUsd`, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 3. RETENTION JOB SYSTEM\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts`\n\n**How It Works**:\n\n1. **Scheduling**: Wall-clock daily trigger (not drifting setInterval)\n   - First check 5 seconds after startup\n   - Periodic checks every 60 seconds\n   - Runs exactly once per UTC calendar day (via `system_kv` persistence)\n\n2. **State Persistence** (in `system_kv` table):\n   - `retention_last_run_date` - YYYY-MM-DD of last run (prevents double-execution)\n   - `retention_last_run_at` - ISO timestamp for health endpoint\n\n3. **Retention Policies** (defined as RetentionPolicy instances):\n   - `execPolicy`: Deletes completed/failed/cancelled executions older than `retentionDays`\n   - `eventsPolicy`: Deletes delivered/skipped/failed events older than `retentionDays`\n   - `stuckEventsPolicy`: Deletes stuck pending/processing events older than `retentionDays * 7` (7x longer grace period)\n   - `dailyMetricsPolicy`: Deletes old daily metrics older than `metricsRetentionDays`\n   - `systemDailyMetricsPolicy`: Deletes system-wide aggregated metrics\n\n4. **Execution Flow**:\n   ```\n   tick() → check if today != lastRunDate\n        ↓\n        → runRetention():\n           ├─ For each tenant:\n           │  ├─ purge persona_executions (status-filtered)\n           │  ├─ purge persona_events (status-filtered)\n           │  ├─ purge stuck events (7-day grace)\n           │  └─ purge daily_metrics\n           │\n           ├─ aggregateSystemMetrics():\n           │  ├─ Read daily_metrics from all tenant DBs\n           │  ├─ Accumulate totals by date\n           │  └─ Upsert into system_daily_metrics\n           │\n           └─ purge system_daily_metrics\n        ↓\n        → persist lastRunDate + lastRunAt\n        ↓\n        → log health metrics (tenantsProcessed, rowsDeleted per table, errors)\n   ```\n\n5. **Chunked Deletion** (via RetentionPolicy.purge()):\n   - Counts total rows & candidates (WHERE created_at < cutoff AND status IN (...))\n   - Aborts if candidates/total > maxPurgeFraction (safety cap, default 0.8)\n   - Deletes in chunks of 5000 rows per batch\n   - Yields event loop between batches (setImmediate) to keep system responsive\n\n**Health Metrics** (RetentionHealth interface):\n```typescript\n{\n  lastRunAt: string | null;\n  lastRunDurationMs: number | null;\n  retentionDays: number;\n  metricsRetentionDays: number;\n  totalRuns: number;\n  totalErrors: number;\n  running: boolean;\n  lastRun: RetentionRunMetrics | null; // detailed per-run stats\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. RETENTION POLICY MECHANISM\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts`\n\n**Architecture**:\n- `RetentionPolicyConfig` interface: `{ table, chunkSize?, deleteFilter? }`\n- Reads spec from TABLE_REGISTRY at construction time (single source of truth)\n- Encapsulates: cutoff logic, safety-fraction checks, chunked delete with yields\n\n**Key Methods**:\n```typescript\nasync purge(\n  db: Database.Database,\n  cutoff: string,              // ISO timestamp for age filtering\n  logger: Logger,\n  context?: Record<string, unknown>\n): Promise<number>             // returns total rows deleted\n```\n\n**Safety Mechanisms**:\n1. Pre-purge sanity check: count total rows vs candidates\n2. Abort if `candidates/total > maxPurgeFraction` (logs error and returns 0)\n3. Chunked delete: prevents long lock durations (~50ms per chunk)\n4. Event-loop yields: keeps system responsive during multi-tenant runs\n\n---\n\n### 5. HTTP API PATTERNS\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` (39,563 bytes)\n\n**Architecture**: Two-tier routing system\n\n**Tier 1: Exact-Path Routes** (O(1) lookup by `METHOD:/path`)\n- Stored in `exactRoutes` Map\n- Used for static endpoints like `/api/status`, `/api/execute`, `/api/oauth/*`, `/api/admin/*`\n- Example: `exactRoutes.set('GET:/api/status', { handler: ... })`\n\n**Tier 2: Resource-Based Routes** (O(1) lookup by `METHOD:resource[:id][:subResource]`)\n- Stored in `resourceRoutes` Map\n- Key function: `resourceKey(method, resource, hasId, subResource)` → `\"METHOD:resource[:id][:subResource]\"`\n- Parsed from URL via `parseRoute(pathname)` → `{ resource, id?, subResource? }`\n- Examples:\n  - `GET /api/personas` → `GET:personas`\n  - `POST /api/personas` → `POST:personas`\n  - `GET /api/personas/{id}` → `GET:personas:id`\n  - `GET /api/personas/{id}/tools` → `GET:personas:id:tools`\n  - `POST /api/personas/{id}/tools` → `POST:personas:id:tools`\n\n**RouteEntry Structure**:\n```typescript\n{\n  handler: RouteHandler;\n  needsDb?: boolean;      // requires tenantDb to be available\n  adminOnly?: boolean;    // requires auth.authType === 'admin'\n}\n```\n\n**Common Handler Signature**:\n```typescript\ntype RouteHandler = (\n  req: http.IncomingMessage,\n  res: http.ServerResponse,\n  ctx: RequestContext,             // { authType, projectId, userEmail }\n  route: ParsedRoute | null,\n  queryString: string | undefined,\n  tenantDb: Database.Database | undefined,\n  scopedProjectId: string | undefined,\n  reqLogger: Logger,\n) => Promise<void> | void;\n```\n\n**Request Processing Flow**:\n1. Parse URL → extract route, query string\n2. Auth check via `auth.validateAndExtractContext(req)`\n3. Determine scoped project (null if admin auth)\n4. Resolve database: single-tenant or per-tenant via TenantDbManager\n5. O(1) exact-path lookup → if hit, call handler\n6. O(1) resource-route lookup via `resourceKey()` → if hit, call handler\n7. Otherwise 404\n\n**Middleware Patterns**:\n- `withHttpAudit(handler, action, resourceType)` - wraps mutation handlers to emit audit events\n- `withScopedEntity(entity, scopedProjectId, res)` - validates ownership + returns entity or sends 404\n- `requireAdmin(ctx, res)` - checks admin access, returns 403 if not\n\n**Error Handling**:\n- Payload too large (>1MB) → 413\n- UNIQUE constraint violation → 409 Conflict\n- Unhandled errors → 500 with `X-Request-Id` header\n\n**Standard Response Format**:\n- `httpUtils.json(res, status, data)` - writes JSON with Content-Type header\n\n---\n\n### 6. TRIGGER SCHEDULER SYSTEM\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts`\n\n**Architecture**: Heap-driven scheduler with in-memory hot path\n\n**Key Components**:\n\n**Heap Data Structure** (`TriggerHeap` in triggerHeap.ts):\n- Min-heap keyed by `nextTriggerAt` (epoch ms)\n- O(log n) push/pop/remove operations\n- Maintains `triggerId → index` Map for O(log n) updates\n- Database remains source of truth; heap is hot-path cache\n\n**Initialization** (Bootstrap Phase):\n1. If `tenantDbManager`: iterate each tenant, load enabled triggers\n2. If single `database`: load all triggers\n3. Populate heap with `{ triggerId, tenantId, nextTriggerAt }`\n4. Log summary: heapSize, duration, failedTenants\n\n**Scheduler Loop**:\n```\nEvery 100-60000ms (computed dynamically):\n  1. Pop all due entries (nextTriggerAt <= now)\n  2. Group by tenantId for batch DB access\n  3. For each tenant:\n     - Fetch triggers by IDs\n     - Skip polling triggers\n     - Detect missed triggers (latency > 60s)\n     - Publish events to persona_events table\n     - Record trigger_fires entry\n     - Compute next trigger time\n     - Push updated time back into heap\n  4. Update metrics (triggersFiredTotal, triggersMissedTotal)\n  5. Schedule next tick based on heap peek (MIN_DELAY_MS, MAX_DELAY_MS)\n```\n\n**Missed Trigger Detection**:\n- Compares scheduled time vs actual fire time\n- Logs warning if latency > MAX_DELAY_MS (60s)\n- Triggers fired late but still recorded\n\n**Metrics** (SchedulerMetrics):\n```typescript\n{\n  heap_size: number;\n  next_due_at: string | null;\n  triggers_fired_total: number;\n  triggers_missed_total: number;\n  avg_tick_latency_ms: number;\n  last_tick_at: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Heartbeat**: Every 60 seconds logs aggregate metrics + per-tick missed counts\n\n**API** (TriggerSchedulerHandle):\n- `close()` - stops scheduler\n- `nudge()` - reschedule immediately (after trigger CRUD)\n- `heapPush(triggerId, tenantId, nextTriggerAt)` - push/update in heap\n- `heapRemove(triggerId)` - remove from heap\n- `getMetrics()` - return current metrics\n\n---\n\n### 7. TENANT DB MANAGER\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/tenantDbManager.ts`\n\n**Architecture**: Per-tenant SQLite database with connection pooling\n\n**Layout**:\n```\n{dataDir}/\n  ├─ system.db           — tenant registry + global state (system_kv, system_daily_metrics)\n  └─ tenants/\n     ├─ {hash1}.db       — tenant 1 database\n     ├─ {hash2}.db       — tenant 2 database\n     └─ ...\n```\n\n**Hash Function**: `crypto.sha256(projectId).slice(0, 16)` — safe filenames\n\n**Connection Pooling**:\n- `CachedDb` interface: `{ db: Database.Database, lastAccess: number }`\n- Maps `projectId → CachedDb`\n- Auto-eviction: idle > 10 minutes (IDLE_EVICT_MS)\n- Eviction check: every 1 minute (EVICT_CHECK_MS)\n\n**Key Methods**:\n1. `getTenantDb(projectId)` — get or create + auto-register in system.db\n2. `getSystemDb()` — access system database\n3. `listTenantIds()` — all registered tenants from system.db\n4. `forEachTenant(fn)` — execute function for each tenant\n5. `getHealthStats()` — per-tenant file size, row counts, oldest record age\n6. `close()` — shutdown all connections + stop eviction timer\n\n**Tenant Registration**:\n- On first `getTenantDb(projectId)` access\n- Inserts into `tenants` table in system.db\n- Calls optional `onTenantCreated` callback for key warming\n\n**Health Stats** (DbHealthStats):\n```typescript\n{\n  totalSizeBytes: number;\n  tenantCount: number;\n  totalExecutionRows: number;\n  totalEventRows: number;\n  oldestUnpurgedAgeMs: number | null;\n  perTenant: Array<{\n    projectId: string;\n    sizeBytes: number;\n    executionRows: number;\n    eventRows: number;\n    oldestRecordAge: string | null;\n  }>;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. TABLE REGISTRY (SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH)\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`\n\n**Purpose**: Declarative classification of time-series tables for retention lifecycle\n\n**Lifecycle Categories**:\n- **Metrizable**: numeric columns aggregated into summary table before purge\n- **Ephemeral**: rows deleted after retention window without pre-purge aggregation\n\n**Registry** (TABLE_REGISTRY constant):\n\n| Table | Lifecycle | Timestamp Column | Metrizable Columns | Aggregation Target | Max Purge % |\n|-------|-----------|------------------|--------------------|--------------------|------------|\n| `persona_executions` | Metrizable | `created_at` | cost_usd (SUM), duration_ms (SUM), input_tokens (SUM), output_tokens (SUM) | `daily_metrics` | 80% |\n| `persona_events` | Ephemeral | `created_at` | — | — | 80% |\n| `audit_events` | Ephemeral | `timestamp` | — | — (90-day min retention) | 80% |\n| `trigger_fires` | Ephemeral | `fired_at` | — | — | 80% |\n| `daily_metrics` | Ephemeral | `date` | — | — | 80% |\n| `system_daily_metrics` | Ephemeral | `date` | — | — | 80% |\n\n**Helper Functions**:\n- `getTableSpec(tableName)` — lookup by name\n- `getTablesByLifecycle(lifecycle)` — filter by category\n- `isMetrizable(spec)` / `isEphemeral(spec)` — type guards\n\n**Design Principle**: Retention engine consults this registry at runtime, not hard-coded in procedural code\n\n---\n\n### 9. ADDITIONAL KEY PATTERNS\n\n**Event-Driven Architecture**:\n- Events published to `persona_events` table with status `'pending'`\n- Event processor picks up pending events and transitions through states\n- Event subscriptions match event types to personas\n- Retry logic with exponential backoff via `retry_after` column\n\n**Multi-Tenancy Model**:\n- Single-tenant mode: one `database` + all personas in `project_id='default'`\n- Multi-tenant mode: `tenantDbManager` with per-tenant DBs\n- Project scoping: queries filter by `project_id` when in user auth context (not admin)\n\n**Trigger Types**:\n- `schedule`: cron expressions or \"every Xm/h/s/d\" shorthand\n- `manual`: triggered by external API call\n- `polling`: checked periodically (not auto-fired by scheduler)\n- `webhook`: received via HTTP POST\n- `chain`: triggered by output of another persona\n\n**Metrics Aggregation**:\n- Per-execution: cost_usd, duration_ms, input/output_tokens recorded in `persona_executions`\n- Per-day rollup: `updateExecution()` auto-increments `daily_metrics` on terminal status transition\n- Per-system: retention job aggregates all tenant `daily_metrics` → `system_daily_metrics`\n\n**Audit Trail** (append-only):\n- Separate database (audit.db) via `AuditLog` class\n- SHA-256 hash chain for integrity verification\n- Discriminated union of entry types (key:encrypt, persona:create, etc.)\n- Query/stats/verify operations via dedicated methods\n\n---\n\n### 10. CRITICAL FILES REFERENCE\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` | All SQL schemas, migrations, DB initialization |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/executions.ts` | Persona execution CRUD, metrics recording |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts` | Daily retention job scheduling & execution |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retentionPolicy.ts` | RetentionPolicy class: safety checks, chunked deletes |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` | HTTP server, exact-path + resource routing |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts` | Heap-driven trigger scheduler |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/tenantDbManager.ts` | Per-tenant DB pool manager |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts` | TABLE_REGISTRY: metrizable/ephemeral lifecycle classification |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/_helpers.ts` | Statement caching, WHERE builders, row mappers |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerHeap.ts` | TriggerHeap: min-heap implementation |\n| `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/index.ts` | Main entry point, component initialization |\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive exploration covers all the architectural patterns, data models, and operational mechanisms of your personas-cloud orchestrator system. Every major component has been analyzed with complete understanding of how data flows through the system, how retention works, how triggers fire, and how HTTP APIs are registered and dispatched."}],"totalDurationMs":93330,"totalTokens":83049,"totalToolUseCount":28,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3618,"cache_read_input_tokens":73983,"output_tokens":5443,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3618},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
